<tr class="">
<td colspan="2" class="" style="text-align:center; font-weight: bold; color: black; background-color: #c9ffd9;">(<i>Braid</i>) <i>Scots</i>, <i>Lallans</i></td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Spoken natively in</th>
<td class="" style=""><a href="United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">United Kingdom</a>, <a href="Republic_of_Ireland" title="Republic of Ireland">Republic of Ireland</a></td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Region</th>
<td class="" style="">Scotland: <a href="Scottish_Lowlands" title="Scottish Lowlands">Scottish Lowlands</a>, <a href="Northern_Isles" title="Northern Isles">Northern Isles</a>, <a href="Caithness" title="Caithness">Caithness</a>, <a href="Isle_of_Arran" title="Isle of Arran">Arran</a> and <a href="Campbeltown" title="Campbeltown">Campbeltown</a><br />
Ulster: <a href="Counties_of_Ireland" title="Counties of Ireland">Counties</a> <a href="County_Down" title="County Down">Down</a>, <a href="County_Antrim" title="County Antrim">Antrim</a>, <a href="County_Londonderry" title="County Londonderry">Londonderry</a> and <a href="County_Donegal" title="County Donegal">Donegal</a></td>
</tr>
<tr class="">
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;">Native speakers</th>
<td class="" style="">100,000 &#160;(1999)<sup id="cite_ref-e16_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-e16-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><br />
1.5 million L2 speakers<sup id="cite_ref-e16_1-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-e16-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><br />
Total: 17%<sup id="cite_ref-Mate_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Mate-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> to 85%<sup id="cite_ref-Public_Attitudes_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Public_Attitudes-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> of the Scottish population speak it to some degree</td>
